             Learning Golf thru Twitter 
           
          
           
              The social media craze has collided with the world of golf instruction - and it's making big waves for teachers and students alike. Can you really improve your scores by using Twitter? You can - 140 characters at a time.            
                        
                     
               
                                     
                       
                          Follow PGA.com on Twitter                       
                   
                                     
                       
                          Like PGA.com on Facebook                       
                   
                                 
           
                   
                 
                                          
                       
             Short Shot Pivot 
           
          
           
              Kentucky PGA Section Teacher of the Year Brian Manzella shows how to generate power with your body rather than your hands to help improve your short game success.           
                        
                     
               
                                     
                       
                                                 
                   
                                 
           
                   
                 
                                          
                       
             A Lesson Learned 
           
          
           
              Four majors, four champions, one lesson to be learned. PGA Vice President Ted Bishop shares some insight from Bermuda on what all golfers can learn from the winners of the year's majors at the PGA Grand Slam of Golf.            
                        
                     
               
                                     
                       
